<p>How does one listen to voices?</p>

<p><em>prelÃºdio, coral e fuga</em> was conceived to be first and foremost about light: shadow, color, reflection. Or rather: about the ways light strikes or bounces off a surface.</p>

<p>Almost all the agogic markings throughout the score refer to a property of how a material refracts light. <em>Iridescente</em> â€” iridescent â€” is the material that changes color depending on the angle at which it is struck by light: sometimes shifting its hue as one gets closer, or quite often spilling the light it reflects into a rainbow.</p>

<p>In adularescence, light seems to inhabit the inside of a gemstone instead, giving off but a warm inner glow.</p>

<p>Caustic means corrosive but at the same time it is also the name of a phenomenon in optics where light is refracted by a curved object, like those dancing rays you get when the sun hits a glass</p>

